		<link>https://github.blog/changelog/2023-11-02-filter-secret-scanning-alerts-by-validity-in-the-alert-list-view</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kevin Duck]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 02 Nov 2023 17:43:25 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">https://github.blog/changelog/2023-11-02-filter-secret-scanning-alerts-by-validity-in-the-alert-list-view</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Filter secret scanning alerts by validity in the alert list view</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://github.blog/changelog/2023-11-02-filter-secret-scanning-alerts-by-validity-in-the-alert-list-view">Filter secret scanning alerts by validity in the alert list view</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://github.blog">The GitHub Blog</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>GitHub Advanced Security users can now filter their secret scanning alerts by validity in the UI at the repository, organization, and enterprise level. Valid statuses are <code>active</code>, <code>inactive</code>, or <code>unknown</code>. <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-cloud@latest/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/enabling-features-for-your-repository/managing-security-and-analysis-settings-for-your-repository#allowing-validity-checks-for-partner-patterns-in-a-repository">Validity checks</a> must be enabled for the repository, organization, or enterprise.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-cloud@latest/code-security/secret-scanning/about-secret-scanning">Learn more about secret scanning</a></li>
<li><a href="https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-cloud@latest/code-security/secret-scanning/managing-alerts-from-secret-scanning#validating-partner-patterns">Learn more about validating partner patterns</a></li>
</ul>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://github.blog/changelog/2023-11-02-filter-secret-scanning-alerts-by-validity-in-the-alert-list-view">Filter secret scanning alerts by validity in the alert list view</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://github.blog">The GitHub Blog</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
